Package com.iciql

iciql (pronounced "icicle") is a Java JDBC SQL statement generator and simple object mapper

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DbUpgrader
    Interface which defines a class to handle table changes based on model versions.
    Filter
    Represents the WHERE clause of a query.
    Iciql
    A class that implements this interface can be used as a database table.
    Iciql.EnumId<X>
    Interface for using the EnumType.ENUMID enumeration mapping strategy.
    SQLDialect
    This interface defines points where iciql can build different statements depending on the database used.
    Token
    Classes implementing this interface can be used as a token in a statement.
    UpdateColumn
    Classes implementing this interface can be used as a declaration in an update statement.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Constants
    Iciql constants.
    Db
    This class represents a connection to a database.
    DbInspector
    Class to inspect a model and a database for the purposes of model validation and automatic model generation.
    DbUpgrader.DefaultDbUpgrader
    The default database upgrader.
    DbVersion
    A system table to track database and table versions.
    Define
    This class provides utility methods to define primary keys, indexes, and set the name of the table.
    Function
    This class provides static methods that represents common SQL functions.
    NestedConditions<T>  
    NestedConditions.And<T>  
    NestedConditions.Or<T>  
    Query<T>
    This class represents a query.
    QueryBetween<T,A>
    This class represents a "between y and z" condition.
    QueryCondition<T,A>
    This class represents a query with an incomplete condition.
    QueryJoin<T>
    This class represents a query with a join.
    QueryJoinCondition<T,A>
    This class represents a query with join and an incomplete condition.
    QueryWhere<T>
    This class represents a query with a condition.
    RuntimeToken
    Represents a traditional PreparedStatment fragment like "id=?, name=?".

    Default implementation of an SQL dialect.

    Derby database dialect.

    MySQL database dialect.
    SQLDialectPostgreSQL
    PostgreSQL database dialect.
    SQLStatement
    This class represents a parameterized SQL statement.
    SubQuery<T,Z>  
    TableDefinition<T>
    A table definition contains the index definitions of a table, the field definitions, the table name, and other meta data.
    TableDefinition.ConstraintForeignKeyDefinition
    The meta data of a constraint on foreign key.
    TableDefinition.ConstraintUniqueDefinition
    The meta data of a unique constraint.
    TableDefinition.IndexDefinition
    The meta data of an index.
    TableInspector
    Class to inspect the contents of a particular table including its indexes.
    TestCondition<A>
    This class represents an incomplete condition.
    UpdateColumnIncrement<T,A>
    This class represents "SET column = (column + x)" in an UPDATE statement.
    UpdateColumnSet<T,A>
    This class represents "SET column = value" in an UPDATE statement.
    ValidationRemark
    A validation remark is a result of running a model validation.

Package com.iciql Description

iciql (pronounced "icicle") is a Java JDBC SQL statement generator and simple object mapper
